
                                            The police's Novela Potelwa says the arrests came after tip-offs from residents.
                                         CAPE TOWN - Nyanga community members have helped police catch a group of robbers that has been terrorising the area. Three teenagers were arrested earlier this week for being in possession of stolen property, including handbags and cellphones. Two suspects involved in a smash and grab incident in Crossroads were also arrested. The police's Novela Potelwa says the arrests came after tip-offs from residents. "They are all expected to appear in court soon. We'd like to commend the communnity for working with the police."